    ('c72f487b-ca1f-49b6-b8ed-235dc2c8d4ea', 'Hollow-Body Rock', 'The hollow-body rock is a bodyweight abdominal exercise performed on the floor. It starts with a hollow-body hold and adds a back-and-forth rock that challenges core stability and increases the difficulty of the movement. It can be performed for time or for reps, either in an ab-focused portion of a workout or as part of a circuit workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It starts with a hollow-body hold and adds a back-and-forth rock that challenges core stability and increases the difficulty of the movement.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('fc36f168-03a6-4867-ae97-6ff086119c11', 'Side Plank Lateral Raise', 'The side plank lateral raise is an exercise that combines an isometric side plank hold with a dumbbell raise to target both the core and the shoulders. You probably won''t be able to use much weight without disrupting your balance, but even at light weight, this is a movement that can help address multiple muscle groups in a time-efficient workout.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'The side plank lateral raise is an exercise that combines an isometric side plank hold with a dumbbell raise to target both the core and the shoulders.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('53d94a1a-7766-40b7-94b9-46e051ef26cb', 'Superhero Burpee', 'The superhero burpee is an advanced variation of the burpee exercise. The main difference between this and the standard burpee is that while on the floor, the hands are extended in front of the body like Superman taking flight. This increases the challenge to the upper back and shoulders. These can be performed for time or reps as part of any fat-loss or athleticism-focused workout or circuit.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The main difference between this and the standard burpee is that while on the floor, the hands are extended in front of the body like Superman taking flight.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
