    ('f07c82c5-6f39-4df3-a569-d8c8f62ae2c7', 'Decline Leg Lift', 'The decline leg lift is a popular bodyweight core exercise targeting the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles, particularly the lower abs. It can be performed for time or for reps as part of the core-focused portion of any workout or circuit.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform decline leg lift with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('f4436f7b-6a42-42f8-a373-3b13621e0fd9', 'Toy Soldier', 'The toy soldier is a calisthenics exercise targeting the hip flexors and legs, which are kicked up one at a time. When each leg is at the top of the kick, the opposing hand touches that foot. It''s a common warm-up exercise before athletics, but can also help raise core temperature and mobilize a wide range of muscles and joints prior to training.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The toy soldier is a calisthenics exercise targeting the hip flexors and legs, which are kicked up one at a time. It''s a common warm-up exercise before athletics, but can also help raise core temperature and mobilize a wide range of muscles and joints prior to training.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('d49aff67-de5f-4b11-b825-71f6319876ed', 'Lateral Ape', 'The lateral ape is an exercise focused on the lower body that involves staying in a low squat position as you hop laterally. It can be performed as part of a dynamic warm-up, to improve hip mobility, or as part of a fat-loss or athleticism-focused circuit workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The lateral ape is an exercise focused on the lower body that involves staying in a low squat position as you hop laterally.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('284bdb0a-880e-4ed4-89c7-a386c1e08e07', 'Hollow-Body Knee Tuck', 'The hollow-body knee tuck is a bodyweight abdominal exercise performed on the floor. It is similar to both the hollow-body hold and the knee tuck or reverse crunch, combining elements of both. It primarily targets the muscles of the rectus abdominis, or “six-pack” muscles. It can be performed for reps or time, either as part of an ab-focused workout or as a component of a circuit workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It is similar to both the hollow-body hold and the knee tuck or reverse crunch, combining elements of both.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('ae6a2efc-ab7a-4f02-96ec-4f36eadc43f4', 'Am Leg Lift', 'The captain''s chair leg raise is an exercise that targets the abs and hip flexors. It involves an apparatus that allows the forearms to rest on pads and the upright torso to hang freely. Unlike the Captain’s chair knee raise, the legs are straight here.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The captain''s chair leg raise is an exercise that targets the abs and hip flexors. Unlike the Captain’s chair knee raise, the legs are straight here.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('d65981be-eb45-4b2a-a72b-00c28f9c8db4', 'Am Decline Abs', 'The decline sit-up is a core exercise that works the iliopsoas, quads, hip flexors, and adductors. The rectus abdominis and obliques are the stabilizers in this movement.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The decline sit-up is a core exercise that works the iliopsoas, quads, hip flexors, and adductors.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('3fb43247-196e-4cd2-9081-9088f682f177', 'Hanging Crunch', 'The hanging crunch an abdominal exercise that targets the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles. It can be performed hanging from a bar, on a dip station or parallel bars, or if grip strength is a limitation, by placing the elbows in ab straps. If hanging from a straight bar is uncomfortable to the wrists or shoulders, you can also perform them hanging with a neutral grip (palms facing one another). It is similar to a hanging knee raise, but with more spinal curling and a more pronounced "crunch" at the top.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It can be performed hanging from a bar, on a dip station or parallel bars, or if grip strength is a limitation, by placing the elbows in ab straps. If hanging from a straight bar is uncomfortable to the wrists or shoulders, you can also perform them hanging with a neutral grip (palms facing one another).', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('e27ded71-ec6c-485b-8104-b33adf290cc3', 'Side Plank', 'The side plank is a popular isometric abdominal exercise focusing on the oblique muscles, as well as the transversus abdominis or deep core muscles. It is sometimes paired with the curl up and bird dog as the “big three” for core strength and stability. It is performed for time and can work in a warm-up or in the core-focused portion of any workout.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform side plank with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('c72e148c-e0d3-46fb-ae74-7edd44599b8d', 'Bird Dog', 'The bird dog is a core exercise designed to help strengthen and stabilize the posterior chain. It involves lifting an opposite-side arm and leg while in a bent-leg tabletop position. It is most commonly performed as part of a dynamic warm-up, or for mobility and muscle activation anytime.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It involves lifting an opposite-side arm and leg while in a bent-leg tabletop position.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('9643a7d7-a420-41db-96bf-cdd9c5987907', 'Single-Leg Curl Up', 'The single-leg curl up is a bodyweight abdominal movement that teaches and reinforces abdominal “bracing” for strength training. It is usually performed along with variations of the bird dog and side plank as the “big three.” The curl up can be performed for time or for reps, with or without pauses at the top position, as part of a warm-up or the core-focused component of any workout.', 3, 2, 7, NULL, 2, '” The curl up can be performed for time or for reps, with or without pauses at the top position, as part of a warm-up or the core-focused component of any workout.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('df2fcce8-064d-4ed0-83fb-eb8cf0fb0ba8', 'Mountain Climber', 'The bench mountain climber is a bodyweight exercise that works the core, shoulders, and lower body while burning a lot of calories. Placing the hands on an elevated surface such as a bench decreases the challenge to the shoulders, allowing lifters to focus their work on the other body parts. Mountain climber variations are usually performed at a fast pace for moderate to high reps, such as 8-12 reps per leg or more.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The bench mountain climber is a bodyweight exercise that works the core, shoulders, and lower body while burning a lot of calories. Placing the hands on an elevated surface such as a bench decreases the challenge to the shoulders, allowing lifters to focus their work on the other body parts.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Bench", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('04cd7fbb-42c3-458b-8a3c-61c9f98b7e32', 'Feet-Elevated Side Plank', 'The feet-elevated bench side plank is an advanced version of the side plank performed with the feet elevated on a bench. It targets the same muscles as the side plank, including the obliques, shoulders, and lateral hips, but the body angle makes it more difficult than side planks on the floor. Most lifters will need to progress to this version after mastering the basic side plank first.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'Most lifters will need to progress to this version after mastering the basic side plank first.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Bench", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('ab40e9e5-6e1e-424f-b9da-564b7ecef16a', 'Cross-Body Sit-Up', 'The cross-body sit-up is a bodyweight exercise targeting the ab muscles, the obliques and rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles in particular. It involves bringing the opposite-side knee and elbow together, usually alternating sides with each rep. It can be performed for time or reps as part of the ab-focused portion of any workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The cross-body sit-up is a bodyweight exercise targeting the ab muscles, the obliques and rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles in particular. It involves bringing the opposite-side knee and elbow together, usually alternating sides with each rep.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('d3e1db65-3e5e-4f26-a067-c8ec2f58513f', 'Decline Kayak', 'The decline kayak is a core exercise targeting the obliques. It involves making a paddling motion on a decline bench with the feet anchored, using a bar or pipe for weight. It is usually performed for moderate to high reps, at least 8-12 reps per side, as part of the ab-focused portion of a workout or circuit.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform decline kayak with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
