    ('c2476481-1bc1-427a-bd39-802fde102e3e', 'Full Moon', 'The full moon is a bodyweight exercise targeting the muscles of the abs. It is similar to a V-up, but with the added challenge of “drawing” a circle shape in the air during each rep. It can be performed for time or reps in the core-focused portion of any workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform full moon with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('cb7ec8b5-7117-47ea-82c5-b5deb2b2f9d1', 'Ab Tuck', 'The hollow-body knee tuck is a bodyweight abdominal exercise performed on the floor. It is similar to both the hollow-body hold and the knee tuck or reverse crunch, combining elements of both. It primarily targets the muscles of the rectus abdominis, or “six-pack” muscles. It can be performed for reps or time, either as part of an ab-focused workout or as a component of a circuit workout.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It is similar to both the hollow-body hold and the knee tuck or reverse crunch, combining elements of both.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('d2e4cc5c-2e19-4933-8794-9e21460c0811', 'Cat-Cow', 'Cat-cow is a traditional yoga pose that is also popular in fitness and strength training. It targets spinal mobility and control of the vertebral column. It can be performed for time or reps as part of a dynamic warm-up or as a mobility or restorative exercise anytime. It can also work as part of a yoga or bodyweight sequence with other poses.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform cat-cow with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('372040b8-eb39-41af-9b60-eda836f9fe9c', 'Crab Walk', 'The crab walk is a full-body exercise that has been popular in schools and gym classes for decades. It''s a full-body coordination challenge that also burns serious calories, making it an excellent inclusion in a full-body warm-up or bodyweight circuit workout.', 3, 6, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform crab walk with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('fd1ec598-8951-43a0-9d3e-a1c1e3fa0b0c', 'Lunge With Overhead Reach', 'The lunge with overhead reach is a full-body bodyweight movement targeting the quads and shoulders. It has both strength and mobility benefits and can be performed one leg at a time or alternating for time or for reps.', 3, 5, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform lunge with overhead reach with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('626c1c51-9e99-4418-a15f-ee842fd8e69f', 'Hang From Bar', 'The hang from bar is a static exercise that involves hanging from a bar by two hands. It can either be an "active hang," where you pack the shoulders and activate the muscles of the upper back, or a "passive hang," where you let the shoulders unpack and let the muscles of the upper body stretch. A passive hang may not be appropriate for all people depending on their shoulder health, but many coaches believe hanging can be healthy for the shoulders when done properly.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'A passive hang may not be appropriate for all people depending on their shoulder health, but many coaches believe hanging can be healthy for the shoulders when done properly.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('7352925b-b7c8-4068-a841-4a3231d26772', 'Hollow Hold', 'The hollow-body hold is an isometric exercise that increases strength and stability in the core muscles. It is common in gymnastics training, CrossFit training, and as a core tension and bracing drill for lifters and athletes of all types. It is performed for time and can be performed as an activation drill prior to lifting, as part of a circuit, or as equipment-free core training anytime.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'The hollow-body hold is an isometric exercise that increases strength and stability in the core muscles. It is common in gymnastics training, CrossFit training, and as a core tension and bracing drill for lifters and athletes of all types.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('84e5d3b7-0a3a-40c4-a7ff-6c6d84841ea8', 'Side Plank Pulse', 'The side plank pulse is a dynamic version of the side plank exercise focusing on the oblique muscles, as well as the transversus abdominis or deep core muscles. It can be performed for time or reps and can work in a warm-up or in the core-focused portion of any workout.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform side plank pulse with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('04c4b3cc-fc89-4dd0-99fd-fd46b3c5adfc', 'Spider Crawl (Unweighted)', 'The spider crawl is a bodyweight exercise that involves crawling on the floor with the knees outside of the elbows. It is different from a leopard crawl in that the hips are higher, and it''s different from a bear crawl because the knees are wider. It can be done as a full-body warm-up, in short bursts for power or circuit training, or for longer durations as cardiovascular conditioning.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform spider crawl (unweighted) with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('f81369bc-5322-4cd3-a8cc-48c681da2f31', 'Hand Shift Plank', 'The hand shift plank is a progression of the straight-arm plank exercise where you maintain a plank position as you shift your hands side to side. The additional movement forces the core muscles to work harder to stabilize.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'The hand shift plank is a progression of the straight-arm plank exercise where you maintain a plank position as you shift your hands side to side.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('5ed8bfbd-d6ae-4c45-88cf-08435652f6cd', 'Cross-Body Plank March', 'The cross-body plank march is an exercise targeting the entire core but especially the obliques. It’s more difficult than a standard plank, with the extra stabilization challenge of bringing one knee at a time off the ground toward the opposing elbow. This will increase the challenge to the core and shoulder muscles, but also present a coordination and balance challenge.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'It’s more difficult than a standard plank, with the extra stabilization challenge of bringing one knee at a time off the ground toward the opposing elbow.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('dd792399-b952-4c00-abcc-d571059928e1', 'Copenhagen Plank', 'The Copenhagen plank is an advanced version of the side plank performed with one foot on a bench and the other foot hovering under it. This exercise targets the same muscles as the side plank, including the obliques, shoulders, and lateral hips, but places extra emphasis on the adductors and is more difficult than side planks on the floor. Most lifters will need to progress to this version after mastering the basic side plank or feet-elevated side plank first.', 3, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'Most lifters will need to progress to this version after mastering the basic side plank or feet-elevated side plank first.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('57ecee50-967c-4edd-b411-13cf39fc5e0f', 'Hanging Leg Tuck', 'The hanging leg tuck is an exercise targeting the entire body, including the arms, upper back, abs, and hip flexors. This specific exercise is part of the new Army Combat Fitness Test or ACFT. It is performe while hanging from a bar and combines elements of a pull-up with a leg raise. Experienced lifters make these look easy, but beginners may need time to build up to sets of 8-12 reps.', 3, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The hanging leg tuck is an exercise targeting the entire body, including the arms, upper back, abs, and hip flexors. It is performe while hanging from a bar and combines elements of a pull-up with a leg raise.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('2c3db20e-75ce-4821-903c-4460f19834a0', 'Alternating Hanging Knee Raise', 'The alternating hanging knee raise is an exercise targeting the abs, but which also works the lats and hip flexors. Rather than performing both legs at a time, you lift one knee at a time and alternate with each rep as if marching in place. Knee raises are often performed for moderate to high reps, such as 8-12 reps or more, as part of ab-focused training.', 3, 2, 7, NULL, 2, 'The alternating hanging knee raise is an exercise targeting the abs, but which also works the lats and hip flexors. Rather than performing both legs at a time, you lift one knee at a time and alternate with each rep as if marching in place.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('65115e3a-5154-433c-8c77-556c81303211', 'Medicine Rotational Throw', 'The medicine ball rotational throw is an explosive exercise targeting the abdominals, including the obliques, as well as the hips and upper back. It involves standing sideways to the wall and twisting the torso to hurl a medicine ball into the wall, then catching the ball on the ricochet. It can be performed for lower reps with a focus on power, or for higher reps with a focus on fat loss and conditioning.', 1, 2, 7, NULL, 2, 'It involves standing sideways to the wall and twisting the torso to hurl a medicine ball into the wall, then catching the ball on the ricochet. It can be performed for lower reps with a focus on power, or for higher reps with a focus on fat loss and conditioning.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('ceeb5434-c1bc-43de-8912-588e917e78b9', 'Hollow-Hold Toss', 'The hollow-hold ball toss is a more difficult version of the hollow-body hold exercise. It involves tossing a ball to a partner while maintaining an isometric hold in the hollow-body position. It can be done for reps or time in any ab-focused workout, or in an "I go, you go" format.', 1, 7, 7, NULL, 2, 'The hollow-hold ball toss is a more difficult version of the hollow-body hold exercise. It involves tossing a ball to a partner while maintaining an isometric hold in the hollow-body position.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('93110823-be2e-45e7-9893-533e8085c9e6', 'Sit-Up With Single-Arm Overhand Throw', 'The sit-up with single-arm overhand throw is an exercise targeting the core muscles, but the inclusion of the throw also brings in other upper-body muscles. When you come to the top of the sit-up position, you throw a medicine ball using one arm to a partner who then throws it right back to you to be caught with both hands. It can be performed for time or reps as part of the ab-focused portion of any workout.', 2, 8, 7, NULL, 2, 'The sit-up with single-arm overhand throw is an exercise targeting the core muscles, but the inclusion of the throw also brings in other upper-body muscles. When you come to the top of the sit-up position, you throw a medicine ball using one arm to a partner who then throws it right back to you to be caught with both hands.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('6e0b4262-bdfc-4d90-8b60-e057f6529286', 'Medicine Partner Twist', 'The medicine ball partner twist is a plyometrics exercise targeting the core muscles, particularly the obliques. You and a partner stand back to back and rotate in unison to pass a medicine ball back and forth on alternating sides.', 2, 8, 7, NULL, 2, 'You and a partner stand back to back and rotate in unison to pass a medicine ball back and forth on alternating sides.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('4e91957e-d041-46a7-b5e0-869f8bddc147', 'Medicine Half Moon', 'The medicine ball half moon is a dynamic core exercise performed around and over a medicine ball or other short, stationary object. It is similar in some ways to a V-up or reverse crunch, and targets both the obliques and the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles. It can be performed for reps or for time, usually in dedicated ab training or as part of a medicine ball and bodyweight circuit workout.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform medicine half moon with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('67600592-e411-4272-8754-e7b6b634b0e8', 'Exercise Roll-Out', 'The exercise ball roll-out is an exercise that strengthens the core, shoulders and upper- back muscles. It starts in a plank-style position, with the arms resting on a ball. Then, roll the ball out in front of you as far as you can while maintaining a strong, neutral spinal position. The lack of stability from the ball increases the degree of difficulty. This is a difficult movement, and beginners may need to use a limited range of motion.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It starts in a plank-style position, with the arms resting on a ball. Then, roll the ball out in front of you as far as you can while maintaining a strong, neutral spinal position.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('6c0d35d2-80d5-49da-990e-82f61e52fc1d', 'Medicine Pass', 'The medicine ball pass is a simple partner-based exercise that involves throwing a weighted ball back and forth. It can be part of a dynamic warm-up for lifting or athletics, but can also work as active rest or as a component of circuit training.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'It can be part of a dynamic warm-up for lifting or athletics, but can also work as active rest or as a component of circuit training.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('44d65fd8-6082-46c5-ab48-f7e27cbcc519', 'Partner Medicine Sit-Up', 'The partner medicine ball sit-up is a more difficult version of the traditional abdominal exercise. Two partners pass a medicine ball back and forth at the top of each rep, so each one must alternate a weighted rep with an unweighted rep. This technique can be done for reps or time in any ab-focused workout, in an "I go, you go" format.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The partner medicine ball sit-up is a more difficult version of the traditional abdominal exercise.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('63d1feae-c9a3-4fee-a0a6-11b2ad34e59f', 'Medicine Russian Twist', 'The medicine ball Russian twist is a weighted version of a popular abdominal training exercise. It targets the oblique muscles, as well as the deep muscles of the core and the rectus abdominis or "six pack" muscles. It can be done for reps or time in the ab-focused portion of any workout.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform medicine russian twist with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('4a31da26-2ea2-40d7-a4af-e4314cc452f5', 'Medicine Slam', 'The medicine ball slam is an explosive exercise for developing power, strength, and speed. Muscles worked include the abdominals, legs, triceps, shoulders, and lats. The slams are usually done in rapid succession to complete one set. It can also be a component of a power or athleticism-focused circuit workout.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform medicine slam with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('dcf2baef-fbcd-497b-8c43-2168be67028f', 'Medicine Twist', 'The medicine ball twist is an exercise targeting the abdominal muscles, particularly the obliques. It is similar in many ways to a Russian twist exercise. The ball is held tight to the chest throughout the movement, and then the torso is rotated from side to side for the desired number of reps or a set amount of time.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The ball is held tight to the chest throughout the movement, and then the torso is rotated from side to side for the desired number of reps or a set amount of time.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Medicine Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('f2e94cfe-a664-4382-83df-93e0bc91a565', 'Decline Oblique Crunch', 'The decline oblique crunch is a popular bodyweight exercise targeting the obliques and the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles. It is usually performed for high reps, such as 10-15 reps per set or more, as part of the ab-focused portion of a workout.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Perform decline oblique crunch with controlled movement, proper form, and full range of motion.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('d74d8ddf-91af-4aef-b867-bcc069fefd45', 'Hanging Windshield Wiper', 'The hanging windshield wiper is an advanced abdominal training exercise that is also extremely challenging to other muscles of the upper body, including the lats (latissimus dorsi), biceps, and grip. It requires—and builds—great strength in the rectus abdominis or "six-pack" muscles, as well as the obliques and deep core muscles. If you can''t perform it hanging from a bar, the lying windshield wiper on the floor provides some of the same benefits.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'The hanging windshield wiper is an advanced abdominal training exercise that is also extremely challenging to other muscles of the upper body, including the lats (latissimus dorsi), biceps, and grip.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('5880c1d6-5090-4102-bf84-b54b5fc7ae9d', 'Exercise Pull-In', 'The exercise ball knee roll-in is an abdominal exercise that involves supporting yourself with your hands in a plank or push-up position and drawing the knees in toward the chest. This is a fairly advanced abdominal move requiring core strength.', 1, 2, 7, NULL, 2, 'The exercise ball knee roll-in is an abdominal exercise that involves supporting yourself with your hands in a plank or push-up position and drawing the knees in toward the chest.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Ball", "IsRequired": true}, {"Name": "Exercise Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('2f98785c-9f23-4298-823b-54b661e6595c', 'Feet-Elevated Crunch', 'The feet-elevated crunch is a variation on the basic crunch, a very popular ab move. Resting the feet on a bench takes some of the hip flexor activation out of the movement, focusing the stress more on the abs. It may have a small range of motion, but this movement produces a major burn.', 1, 1, 7, NULL, 2, 'Resting the feet on a bench takes some of the hip flexor activation out of the movement, focusing the stress more on the abs.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Exercise Ball", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
