    ('c052b21d-854f-4f85-bbc3-2c66b7da12d3', 'Weighted Push-Up', 'The plate-weighted push-up is a simple way to make a classic bodyweight exercise more difficult. It targets all the same muscles as the push-up: chest, triceps, shoulders, upper back, and core. You can balance a plate on your upper back yourself, but it''s easier and safer to have someone else put it there. If you stack a few plates up, be sure to have a spotter close at hand.', 1, 1, 1, 5, 2, 'The plate-weighted push-up is a simple way to make a classic bodyweight exercise more difficult. It targets all the same muscles as the push-up: chest, triceps, shoulders, upper back, and core.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Dumbbell", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
    ('fdcf2b98-bf53-462a-bea3-e129cd71449e', 'Chest Dip', 'The chest dip is a bodyweight exercise performed on parallel bars or on a pull-up and dip station. It targets the chest, triceps, and shoulders. Dips with a chest focus are usually performed with the torso leaning forward and the elbows angled out from the torso. Dips can be performed for low reps for strength or higher reps for muscle growth.', 1, 1, 1, 5, 2, 'The chest dip is a bodyweight exercise performed on parallel bars or on a pull-up and dip station. Dips with a chest focus are usually performed with the torso leaning forward and the elbows angled out from the torso.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[]'::text),
    ('add2458e-d732-4e05-80d1-80690e963aa0', 'Pass-Through Stretch With', 'The pass-through stretch with band is a popular move to build and maintain mobility in the shoulder joint and to strengthen the muscles of the upper back and rotator cuff. It is common in CrossFit and Olympic lifting training and is usually performed as part of a warm-up or paired with movements in a workout. It can also be performed with a PVC pipe or dowel if a band isn''t available.', 4, 9, 1, 5, 1, 'It is common in CrossFit and Olympic lifting training and is usually performed as part of a warm-up or paired with movements in a workout.', NULL, true, NULL, '2026-01-18 00:00:00.000 +0000'::timestamp with time zone, '[{"Name": "Band", "IsRequired": true}]'::text),
